text.tspan: My Name is Patrick Richter, I am a physics student and and I am currently
looking for a master thesis subject.
In the last years I have mainly moved my focus from physics to informatics.
I have done that because I am working on a particular project and was trying
to gain the necessary technical knowledge that is needed to implement it.
My goal is to implement an chat server that works like an mind map and
can be navigated using a web browser
It also should have the feature to combine nodes with the same content.
If two users ask the same question at different places without knowing
from each other and a third user marks the post as identical they should
Right now I am looking for a way to combine this project with my physics
master thesis. For me personally building the chat server (that consumes a
lot of my time) has a higher priority than my degree but it would be nice if
I also could finish my master.
One idea for a subject of a possible master thesis is to discuss different
possibilities of displaying the relationships between theories and physical
phenomena as a mind map and test them on real problems.
